                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "What would the nurse anticipate when evaluating for the effects of raloxifene in an older client?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nRaloxifene is an estrogen receptor modulator. It was developed to limit the side and adverse effects of estrogen while producing beneficial effects. The purpose of this medication is to increase bone mineral density. Leg tenderness or cramps can indicate deep vein thrombosis, which is an adverse effect of raloxifene. The modulating effects of this medication can lead to hot flashes and vaginal bleeding.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, the therapeutic effect of this medication. Note that a decrease in the severity of hot flashes and resumption of the menstrual cycle are hormone-related effects that will not be seen in an older client who is taking this medication for osteoporosis. In addition, leg cramps and tenderness can be eliminated because they suggest deep vein thrombosis, which would be an adverse effect of this medication. Recalling that this medication is an estrogen receptor modulator used for osteoporosis will assist in directing you to the correct option.",
                        "id": "1af4c5eb5b9f47b4a10735287e8ed0b5",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "3759f810cd064394a6253e17238f68d5",
                                "content": "With meals"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "96ac3d5ef87a410bbde9116a61b0c7d7",
                                "content": "Every 4 hours"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "3d7a310278e04e92a816447c744265b7",
                                "content": "Just before meals"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "03c5e80d75a24230b91fd4ed22e1ea66",
                                "content": "1 hour after meals"
                            }
                        ],
