                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nCalcium carbonate is best administered 1 to 1½ hours after meals. The tablets need to be given with a full glass of water. Therefore, options 2, 3, and 4 are incorrect times and methods for administration.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nEliminate options 2, 3, and 4 because they are comparable or alike and indicate that the medications would be taken with food. Remember that it is best to take calcium carbonate 1 to 1½ hours after meals.",
